87
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,029
The statement also grieved the death of

88
00:03:30,029 --> 00:03:33,799
a famous Uighur musician and poet, Abdurehim
Heyit.

89
00:03:33,799 --> 00:03:36,900
He’s been detained in China since 2017.

90
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:37,900


91
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,029
Heyit is incredibly popular in the Turkic
world for his art.

92
00:03:41,029 --> 00:03:43,499
So, what was the Chinese regime’s response?

93
00:03:43,499 --> 00:03:47,469
The report of his death was greatly exaggerated.

94
00:03:47,469 --> 00:03:48,870
China released this video,

95
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:51,460
